text: Josef Kahl (31 March 1913 - 23 February 1942) was a Czech ski jumper. He competed in the individual event at the 1936 Winter Olympics. He was killed in action during World War II. ==References== Category:1913 births Category:1942 deaths Category:Czech male ski jumpers Category:Olympic ski jumpers of Czechoslovakia Category:Ski jumpers at the 1936 Winter Olympics Category:People from Harrachov Category:Czechoslovak military personnel killed in World War II
